Interface ClassType

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, Copy<TypeObject>, Declaration, Importable, MemberInstance, Named, Qualifier, ReferenceType, java.io.Serializable, Type, TypeObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
DiamondType, IntersectionType, JL5ClassType, JL5ParsedClassType, JL5SubstClassType, JL5SubstType, LubType, ParsedClassType, RawClass
All Known Implementing Classes:
ClassType_c, DiamondType_c, IntersectionType_c, JL5ClassType_c, JL5ParsedClassType_c, JL5SubstClassType_c, LubType_c, ParsedClassType_c, RawClass_c, SubstClassType_c
public interface ClassType
extends Importable, ReferenceType, MemberInstance, Declaration
A ClassType represents a class, either loaded from a classpath, parsed from a source file, or obtained from other source. A ClassType is not necessarily named.
